    parentName: "div"
  }, "Image by Leonardo Toshiro Okubo on Unsplash")), mdx("p", null, "In practice, part of the conference was in Slovak, while the English-speaking guests did not understand anything. At other times, the meeting was purely in English, and several Slovaks may have had trouble understanding it. There were even moments when the host tried to interpret Slovak passages into English and vice versa. This approach was inefficient and time-consuming. However, I must praise her; she has a very good level of English."), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "It is necessary to specify one language for the conference")), mdx("p", null, "The conference should not be multilingual. It will do more harm than good. When I was asked to speak, I didn\u2019t know in which language. The others were in a similar situation. And what I said was often translated by someone else."), mdx("p", null, "If we want to have guests from abroad at the conference, we could have the whole meeting in English. However, if we want to do training mainly for Slovaks and Czechs, Slovak can be the main language. In this case, English guests would only attend selected workshops in English if someone would organize them. However, the workshops are already separate, all participants have a predetermined language, and therefore, it can work."), mdx("p", null, "I rate the host\u2019s performance as good. She seemed energetic and set the tone for the whole event. However, I definitely see room for improvement. Before the first workshop was supposed to start (the delay was already over 18 minutes), we waited for a certain Richard. He was to introduce himself as the incoming Area Director. He either had technical problems or was not even at the computer at the moment. However, the host lost perhaps five minutes by repeatedly calling him."), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "If you call someone to speak up to the microphone and they don\u2019t answer, move on. They got a chance and didn\u2019t took it. Others shouldn\u2019t have to wait.")), mdx("p", null, "It is this moment that I perceive as her greatest failure. It seemed very unprofessional. When I host an event, I try to stick to the agenda, but I have learned to react flexibly. In this case, I would open the workshop section and give Richard space one more time after it was over. It doesn\u2019t matter if there are fewer participants connected. It is not my fault as a host if someone is not present. Especially if they know in advance that they will speak. If I let them speak afterward, I do them a favor."), mdx("h2", {
    "id": "technical-solution"
  }, "Technical solution"), mdx("p", null, "The organizers chose ", mdx("a", _extends({
