  }, {
    "href": "https://zoom.us/",
    "target": "_blank",
    "rel": "noreferrer"
  }), "Zoom"), " as the platform. That is understandable, as they have the most experience with it. They also used it to organize competitions and have now applied this know-how to this training. What I was most curious about was how the workshops would take place. According to the agenda, up to three workshops were to take place simultaneously."), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "breakout-rooms"
  }, "Breakout rooms"), mdx("p", null, "The organizers have chosen the lesser-known Zoom feature, called \u201Cbreakout rooms.\u201D When you join Zoom, you\u2019ll be in the main room, where the main track, which is common to all, takes place. However, the \u201Czoom master\u201D can move you from there to the new virtual rooms. In the case of workshops, there were three."), mdx("p", null, "These rooms have most of the main room features, including the ability to share a presentation. During the training, they were only open for a predetermined time (a countdown was running on the screen), and the administrator kept us informed about how much time we had left."), mdx("p", null, "On the one hand, several workshops seemed to be cut in the middle, but we followed the schedule exactly thanks to that. Simply put, the room closes, and you move further in the program."), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "naming-scheme"
  }, "Naming scheme"), mdx("p", null, "In order for the organizers to be able to move us to the trainings we were interested in, they required us to name ourselves according to a certain scheme. This was clearly explained in the meeting agenda and during the break on the main room screen. The scheme looked something like this:"), mdx("pre", null, mdx("code", _extends({
    parentName: "pre"
  }, {}), "SEC_SK_A2_B2_Vladim\xEDr_Z\xE1hradn\xEDk\n")), mdx("ul", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "The first part, ", mdx("inlineCode", {
    parentName: "li"
  }, "SEC"), ", is the role I will represent as a club officer. In this case, the Secretary. However, nothing prevented me from using the abbreviation of another role. If I wanted to participate in PR training, I would use the abbreviation VPPR"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "SK is the preferred language in which I would like to undergo training. The options were: SK (Slovak), CZ (Czech), and EN (English)"), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ul"
  }, "A2 and B2 tell the organizers which workshops I want to go to. Their overview and relevant codes were included in the agenda and allowed everyone to put together a tailor-made training")), mdx("p", null, "In a perfect world, all participants would be named as instructed. When you have people named like that, they are also lined up in Zoom, and you can move them en masse to other rooms. However, in reality, I\u2019ve noticed that many have either not been renamed at all or been named incorrectly."), mdx("p", null, "For example, if they serve as Vice President Education and Secretary, they put VPE", mdx("em", {
    parentName: "p"
  }, "SEC"), " in their name. But to which workshop should you assign them in such a case? I would probably choose based on which code is first."), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
    parentName: "blockquote"
  }, "Never expect everyone to follow your instructions to the letter")), mdx("p", null, "During the meeting, the presenter emphasized the importance of naming yourself correctly. The organizers had to address all those who didn\u2019t meet it on an ongoing basis. In general, the solution worked, but it was far from ideal."), mdx("h3", {
    "id": "video-loop-with-an-agenda"
  }, "Video loop with an agenda"), mdx("p", null, "I praise that during the breaks, the organizers broadcast the complete agenda and all the necessary instructions in the loop. They prepared a 10-minute video that blended between the two screens. The instructions were bilingual \u2014 in Slovak and English. However, I was a little annoyed that we saw the window frame of the VLC player the whole time."), mdx("p", null, "Since I know the organizers, I assume that they used the ", mdx("a", _extends({
